          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 12,
              "href": "http://sevenpillarsinstitute.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Income-Inequality.jpg",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 5,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "af9892f07808_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b106",
          "text": "Inequality drives status insecurity and the advertising industry plays on that to fuel the consumerism that is destroying the planet and with it the basis for all human wealth. Tragically, it is now also clear that all this over-consumption is not making us any happier. “The link between economic development and real improvements in quality of life is broken in rich societies” (Wilkinson and Pickett, 2014). Inequality has devastating health impacts, which in turn result in massive economic costs to the health systems of unequal countries.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "af9892f07808_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "64fb",
          "text": "“Overall levels of health are far worse in more economically unequal societies. Research suggest that life expectancy is longer and rates of adult mortality, infant mortality, mental illness and obesity are lower in more equal societies.” — Equality Trust, 2015",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 255,
              "href": "https://www.equalitytrust.org.uk/health",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 241,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 239,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "af9892f07808_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4f27",
          "text": "Inequality is a huge social, health and economic problem — not only within countries but also between nations. In the next chapter we will take a closer look at the economic mechanisms of re-distribution of wealth (or more precisely the transfer of wealth from the poor (many) to the rich (few) — a system that operates both within and between countries. Here is a link to a well produced video by the activist organization ‘The Rules’ which aims to encourage people to take an active role in the re-design of an economic systems that does not serve humanity or the planets: Global Wealth Inequality — What you never knew you never knew (3:50min.).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 434,
              "href": "http://therules.org/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 425,
              "title": "",
