          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "af9892f07808_24",
          "href": null,
          "name": "54e8",
          "text": "Many of our common household products, like plastic containers (bottled water), cosmetics such as sun-screen, detergents and disinfectants, all contain chemical compounds that act as so called endocrine disruptors which can have severe effects on humans and wildlife by affecting reproductive health and the development of the nervous system (more information).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 359,
              "href": "http://www.beyondpesticides.org/health/endocrine.pdf",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 343,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "af9892f07808_25",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5566",
          "text": "A recent World Health Organization report links these compounds to the rise in endocrine related diseases like genital malformation in both sexes, reduction in semen quality and fertility, adverse pregnancies, neurobehavioural disorders, various types of cancers, and the massive increase in type-2 diabetes (WHO, 2012).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 318,
              "href": "http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/78102/1/WHO_HSE_PHE_IHE_2013.1_eng.pdf?ua=1",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 309,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "af9892f07808_26",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b2f7",
          "text": "Furthermore, the industrial production of hazardous chemicals such as pesticides also carries significant risks as a result of industrial accidents. The most serious of these, the Bhopal disaster in India, occurred when a pesticide plant released 40 tons of methyl isocyanate gas, an intermediate chemical in the production of pesticides. The disaster immediately killed nearly 3,000 people and ultimately caused at least 15,000 deaths.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
